Realising they might not succeed in their bid to oust President Cyril Ramaphosa at the upcoming national executive committee (NEC) meeting, his opponents have not stopped searching for a reason to remove him. They now claim he paid to be elected at the ANC national conference at Nasrec in 2017. Supporters of former president Jacob Zuma are demanding Ramaphosa and the NEC must be investigated for being elected fraudulently and say their decisions were not legitimate until this matter was cleared. The Gauteng Radical Economic Transformation President Jacob Zuma Support Group, as they call themselves, alleged the current ANC government...